WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.006 --> 00:00:09.301
[♪ epic theme music playing]

2
00:00:11.000 --> 00:00:17.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

3
00:01:54.906 --> 00:01:57.908
-[♪ soft music playing]
-[waves crashing]

4
00:02:08.169 --> 00:02:10.088
[Lord Piper]
Another crossing burned.

5
00:02:10.130 --> 00:02:11.673
We might never
reach Tumbleton.

6
00:02:12.591 --> 00:02:15.052
So how long will it take you
to build the bloody thing again?

7
00:02:15.093 --> 00:02:18.388
[scoffs] We will have to find
another crossing.

8
00:02:18.388 --> 00:02:20.974
-take the long way round.
-The queen will abhor
this delay.

9
00:02:22.559 --> 00:02:24.645
-[spitting]
-Lord Piper. take 100
of your fastest riders

10
00:02:24.686 --> 00:02:26.103
-and make for Stoney Sept.
-[metal scraping]

11
00:02:26.146 --> 00:02:27.606
Secure the barge
and transit there.

12
00:02:28.690 --> 00:02:30.609
-[metal continues scraping]
-That puts us back by a week.

13
00:02:30.651 --> 00:02:31.943
but we can do no better.

14
00:02:31.985 --> 00:02:33.904
It's our last chance
to ford the river

15
00:02:33.945 --> 00:02:35.530
with an army of this size.

16
00:02:37.449 --> 00:02:39.451
[groaning]

17
00:02:44.414 --> 00:02:47.125
-[cane thuds]
-Will we continue
to suffer this Cole

18
00:02:47.167 --> 00:02:49.628
and his band
of hangers-on?

19
00:02:49.670 --> 00:02:52.756
They flit about us
like fucking deer flies.

20
00:02:52.798 --> 00:02:55.801
another thing that we
do not endure in the North.

21
00:02:55.841 --> 00:02:57.552
Better deer flies
than frostbite.

22
00:02:58.804 --> 00:03:01.264
But Criston Cole
I am past enduring.

23
00:03:01.306 --> 00:03:02.766
North or South.

24
00:03:02.808 --> 00:03:06.269
Then loose my wolves
and me on the hunt.

25
00:03:06.311 --> 00:03:08.397
and we will bring him down.

26
00:03:09.815 --> 00:03:11.400
Or we could play
at his game.

27
00:03:12.359 --> 00:03:14.361
[people chattering]

28
00:03:17.864 --> 00:03:19.866
[laughter]

29
00:03:22.577 --> 00:03:24.287
[metal clanging]

30
00:03:24.329 --> 00:03:26.039
[footsteps approaching]

31
00:03:26.081 --> 00:03:28.083
-[thud]
-[footsteps receding quickly]

32
00:03:41.096 --> 00:03:42.555
-[blade unsheathing]
-[grunting]

33
00:03:48.186 --> 00:03:49.396
[soldier]
Ambush!

34
00:03:50.522 --> 00:03:52.524
[soldiers shouting]

35
00:03:54.942 --> 00:03:56.528
[soldier]
We're under attack!

36
00:04:00.741 --> 00:04:02.159
To the next crossing. then?

37
00:04:02.200 --> 00:04:03.994
They'll make for Stoney Sept

38
00:04:04.035 --> 00:04:05.746
and we'll once more
be ahead of them.

39
00:04:05.787 --> 00:04:08.540
-Fall back!
-[soldiers shouting]

40
00:04:14.045 --> 00:04:16.047
[thunder rumbling]

41
00:04:19.551 --> 00:04:20.886
[goat bleating]

42
00:04:44.284 --> 00:04:46.411
If I'd have known
we were expecting guests.

43
00:04:46.453 --> 00:04:48.205
I would have made up the beds.

44
00:04:48.246 --> 00:04:49.790
We're looking for
Aemond Targaryen.

45
00:04:49.831 --> 00:04:52.250
-the Kinslayer.
-Ah. yes.
There's been a horde of you

46
00:04:52.292 --> 00:04:56.087
since the ungrateful queen
announced her bounty.

47
00:04:56.797 --> 00:04:59.382
Well. you won't find
your quarry here.

48
00:04:59.424 --> 00:05:01.885
There's an old man
who churns the butter.

49
00:05:01.927 --> 00:05:04.137
but he's blind in both eyes.

50
00:05:05.180 --> 00:05:08.225
And the boy
who feeds the horses.

51
00:05:08.266 --> 00:05:10.727
-And then there are the ghosts.
-[thunder rumbling]

52
00:05:10.769 --> 00:05:14.105
Seems you have not learned
the history of this place

53
00:05:14.147 --> 00:05:16.191
and the laborers who built it...

54
00:05:18.026 --> 00:05:20.862
who died here in chains...

55
00:05:21.822 --> 00:05:23.448
in service to
Harren the Cruel.

56
00:05:23.490 --> 00:05:25.283
-[thunder crashing]
-[gasping]

57
00:05:28.620 --> 00:05:30.163
This castle breathes.

58
00:05:35.627 --> 00:05:39.214
She swallows the greedy.
the heedless.

59
00:05:42.509 --> 00:05:45.971
Her founding stones
were watered with
the blood of men.

60
00:05:48.014 --> 00:05:49.975
And she's always thirsty.

61
00:05:52.853 --> 00:05:55.105
[rocks clattering]

62
00:05:55.105 --> 00:05:58.859
-[bats screeching]
-[sellswords screaming]

63
00:06:08.577 --> 00:06:10.161
Oi! You bloody craven?!

64
00:06:12.330 --> 00:06:13.832
Fuck this place.

65
00:06:18.336 --> 00:06:20.338
[person screaming]

66
00:06:21.256 --> 00:06:23.258
[screams echoing]

67
00:06:24.885 --> 00:06:27.846
[maniacal laughter echoing]

68
00:06:29.222 --> 00:06:30.682
[Alys] Can you hear me?

69
00:06:32.767 --> 00:06:34.394
Stay back! Stay back!

70
00:06:35.520 --> 00:06:39.065
My-- my brother.
Aegon. he was here.

71
00:06:39.107 --> 00:06:40.859
His face was on fire.
[grunting]

72
00:06:41.735 --> 00:06:43.695
I saw him.
He was clutching at me.

73
00:06:43.737 --> 00:06:46.197
dragging me down
into the dark.

74
00:06:46.239 --> 00:06:49.200
-My-- my brother.
-It's just the dream again.
That's all.

75
00:06:49.242 --> 00:06:51.244
[softly shushing]

76
00:06:54.581 --> 00:06:56.917
It's just the dream again.

77
00:06:56.957 --> 00:06:58.460
[knife clattering]

78
00:07:05.884 --> 00:07:08.053
She saw it.

79
00:07:08.094 --> 00:07:12.057
She said I would die.
that I ruined everything.

80
00:07:12.098 --> 00:07:13.308
No.

81
00:07:16.895 --> 00:07:18.897
[softly shushing]

82
00:07:23.109 --> 00:07:24.861
[whispering] Mother.

83
00:07:24.903 --> 00:07:26.905
[humming softly]

84
00:07:31.785 --> 00:07:34.788
[humming continues. echoing]

85
00:07:39.417 --> 00:07:41.252
[cats mewing]

86
00:07:45.423 --> 00:07:47.425
[people chattering]

87
00:07:55.517 --> 00:07:57.727
None may enter.
save at our queen's direction.

88
00:07:57.769 --> 00:08:01.022
It is a matter
of some delicacy.

89
00:08:02.565 --> 00:08:06.111
I'm not certain how familiar you
are with disorders of the. um...

90
00:08:07.195 --> 00:08:09.572
female persuasion.

91
00:08:09.614 --> 00:08:10.699
Hm?

92
00:08:15.286 --> 00:08:16.871
[door opens]

93
00:08:24.295 --> 00:08:28.091
I must thank you again
for your loyalty. Grand Maester.

94
00:08:28.133 --> 00:08:30.260
I flatter myself to think
that I have ever been

95
00:08:30.260 --> 00:08:32.220
a faithful servant
to Your Grace.

96
00:08:33.179 --> 00:08:35.390
More than that.
you've been a friend.

97
00:08:37.642 --> 00:08:39.227
But we have now
a new queen.

98
00:08:41.145 --> 00:08:44.941
And I find myself
under some scrutiny.

99
00:08:44.983 --> 00:08:47.610
I fear I can
no longer offer you

100
00:08:47.652 --> 00:08:50.113
assistance after today

101
00:08:50.155 --> 00:08:52.365
without making
the proper disclosures.

102
00:08:54.325 --> 00:08:55.493
I understand.

103
00:09:05.920 --> 00:09:07.380
[door opens]

104
00:09:08.089 --> 00:09:09.340
[door closes]

105
00:09:10.175 --> 00:09:11.676
I don't want it.

106
00:09:12.844 --> 00:09:13.887
You must.

107
00:09:14.929 --> 00:09:17.307
It could be a boy.
Do you see?

108
00:09:17.348 --> 00:09:19.184
Aegon's heir.
a rival to Joffrey.

109
00:09:20.185 --> 00:09:21.770
To Rhaenyra herself.

110
00:09:26.858 --> 00:09:29.069
She will kill it.
She will have no choice.

111
00:09:30.570 --> 00:09:32.155
Or if she does not.
she will take it from you.

112
00:09:32.197 --> 00:09:34.574
Aemond still lives.
as far as we know.

113
00:09:34.616 --> 00:09:35.867
He's at Harrenhal.

114
00:09:35.909 --> 00:09:37.660
No. he was there.
but he has fled.

115
00:09:37.702 --> 00:09:39.913
-He's vanished.
-I have seen him.

116
00:09:41.122 --> 00:09:44.250
He burns.
but without fire.

117
00:09:50.381 --> 00:09:53.176
If Aemond threatens
Rhaenyra's rule.

118
00:09:53.218 --> 00:09:55.220
she will use the child
as her shield.

119
00:09:56.554 --> 00:09:58.848
I can't do it.

120
00:09:58.890 --> 00:10:00.725
Helaena. please.
Please.

121
00:10:01.893 --> 00:10:03.812
For your own sake.
do you not wish to be free?

122
00:10:04.813 --> 00:10:06.064
I can't.

123
00:10:07.565 --> 00:10:10.068
-No. No.
-Think of it. think of it
as a cup of tea.

124
00:10:10.110 --> 00:10:11.694
Nothing more.

125
00:10:11.736 --> 00:10:13.363
But it isn't.

126
00:10:13.404 --> 00:10:15.615
No. No. it's not.
Listen to me.

127
00:10:15.657 --> 00:10:17.033
Listen to me.
it is a blessing.

128
00:10:17.075 --> 00:10:18.284
It is a remedy

129
00:10:18.326 --> 00:10:19.953
taught to the masters
of the Citadel.

130
00:10:20.954 --> 00:10:23.540
It has delivered me
from disgrace and ruin.

131
00:10:23.581 --> 00:10:26.042
It has delivered Rhaenyra
herself when she was young.

132
00:10:26.084 --> 00:10:27.669
And it will deliver you. too.

133
00:10:29.587 --> 00:10:30.964
-Helaena. Please. please.
-No.

134
00:10:31.005 --> 00:10:33.049
Listen to me.

135
00:10:33.091 --> 00:10:34.759
Will you bear a child

136
00:10:34.801 --> 00:10:38.054
who will be never more
than a hostage or a pawn?

137
00:10:38.096 --> 00:10:39.264
It's mine!

138
00:10:40.431 --> 00:10:42.350
It's my own. it's mine!

139
00:10:43.977 --> 00:10:44.978
[sighs]

140
00:10:48.731 --> 00:10:50.817
I had hoped
a seat on the council
would suffice

141
00:10:50.859 --> 00:10:52.902
as recompense for
House Frey's loyalty.

142
00:10:52.944 --> 00:10:55.113
But Harrenhal
was to be our recompense.

143
00:10:55.155 --> 00:10:57.240
payment for giving
your Winter Wolves

144
00:10:57.282 --> 00:11:00.076
passage across the Twins.
promised by your own son.

145
00:11:00.118 --> 00:11:02.453
-My son is dead.
-And now. I discover

146
00:11:02.495 --> 00:11:05.165
that you have pledged
our castle as a trophy.

147
00:11:05.206 --> 00:11:07.417
free to any hedge knight
who can bring you the head

148
00:11:07.417 --> 00:11:09.961
-of Aemond Targaryen.
-You. yourself.
are welcome to try.

149
00:11:10.003 --> 00:11:12.630
Cregan Stark's army
has crossed the Trident.

150
00:11:12.672 --> 00:11:15.925
and we expect the crown's
word to be honored.

151
00:11:15.967 --> 00:11:18.595
no matter
if some grubby sellsword

152
00:11:18.636 --> 00:11:21.389
has dubbed himself
Lord of Harrenhal
in the meanwhile.

153
00:11:26.644 --> 00:11:28.354
For now. however.

154
00:11:28.396 --> 00:11:31.065
I would be pleased
to join Your Grace's council.

155
00:11:37.238 --> 00:11:39.782
[Manderly]
What could anyone possibly
want in Wendish Town?

156
00:11:39.782 --> 00:11:42.452
-[cat meowing]
-[Addam] Not Wendish Town
itself. Your Grace.

157
00:11:42.493 --> 00:11:44.287
but a small village
at the outskirts.

158
00:11:44.329 --> 00:11:45.955
There were
several farms burned.

159
00:11:45.997 --> 00:11:48.540
and the men we talked to were
certain it was Vhagar herself.

160
00:11:48.583 --> 00:11:51.002
[whispering]
The Sea Snake's bastard.
now a dragonrider.

161
00:11:51.044 --> 00:11:52.879
-That's his brother.
-[Rhaenyra]
Lord Darry is our ally.

162
00:11:52.921 --> 00:11:55.215
Aemond may be
provoking us.

163
00:11:55.256 --> 00:11:57.550
By sacking a farm or three?
To what end?

164
00:11:57.592 --> 00:11:59.052
[Daemon]
Dragons need to eat.

165
00:11:59.093 --> 00:12:00.637
[whispering]
The White Worm. she was called.

166
00:12:00.678 --> 00:12:03.056
But they are fugitives.
We will root them out
soon enough.

167
00:12:03.097 --> 00:12:05.099
-The whore.
-Mm-hmm.

168
00:12:10.230 --> 00:12:12.649
There was
a skirmish last night
at the Dragon Gate.

169
00:12:12.690 --> 00:12:14.234
Horses were required
to dispel it.

170
00:12:14.275 --> 00:12:15.818
If only the Lady Mysaria
had been there

171
00:12:15.860 --> 00:12:17.820
with her promised bread
and ladlefuls of stew.

172
00:12:17.862 --> 00:12:20.657
Or if. by some miracle.
the king consort's City Watch

173
00:12:20.698 --> 00:12:22.992
had shown a penny's
worth of restraint

174
00:12:23.034 --> 00:12:24.744
pursuing the pettiest of crimes.

175
00:12:24.786 --> 00:12:27.413
-the pettiest of criminals--
-Did anyone see
where Vhagar flew?

176
00:12:27.455 --> 00:12:29.249
We went with all speed
to take up the trail.

177
00:12:29.290 --> 00:12:30.708
but it was two days cold.

178
00:12:30.750 --> 00:12:32.585
Once again.
Aemond is nowhere to be found.

179
00:12:32.627 --> 00:12:34.003
Two of our gold cloaks
were found dead

180
00:12:34.045 --> 00:12:36.339
in the street this morning.

181
00:12:36.381 --> 00:12:38.508
Put to the blade
by an unknown hand.

182
00:12:38.549 --> 00:12:39.676
Where was this?

183
00:12:39.717 --> 00:12:42.011
-Flea Bottom.
-Flea Bottom.

184
00:12:42.011 --> 00:12:44.013
Mm. has ever been
a realm unto itself.

185
00:12:44.055 --> 00:12:47.892
Quite ungovernable.
full of undesirables.

186
00:12:47.934 --> 00:12:51.187
[Rhaenyra]
Vhagar appears while
Ormund Hightower

187
00:12:51.229 --> 00:12:53.273
gathers himself at Tumbleton
to some hidden purpose.

188
00:12:53.314 --> 00:12:55.400
We need not waste our sweat
fretting over a fox

189
00:12:55.441 --> 00:12:57.193
gone to ground.
If you will not burn him...

190
00:12:57.235 --> 00:12:58.695
-He is not a f--
-...then my army

191
00:12:58.736 --> 00:13:00.071
will root him out
soon enough.

192
00:13:00.113 --> 00:13:02.031
[Orwyle] As to that.
there is fresh news

193
00:13:02.073 --> 00:13:04.242
from Lord Tully's camp.

194
00:13:04.284 --> 00:13:06.202
Their march has been slowed
by interference

195
00:13:06.244 --> 00:13:08.413
from Ser Criston Cole
and his men.

196
00:13:08.454 --> 00:13:11.666
River crossings are being burned
before the army can reach them.

197
00:13:11.708 --> 00:13:13.293
Go back to the Riverlands.

198
00:13:13.334 --> 00:13:15.420
If Aemond has
shown himself once.
he may do so again.

199
00:13:15.461 --> 00:13:18.214
Take no risk.
but ascertain his path.
his purpose.

200
00:13:18.256 --> 00:13:19.716
If I may. Your Grace.

201
00:13:19.757 --> 00:13:22.802
We arrived back
only this morning.

202
00:13:22.844 --> 00:13:25.054
The Lady Baela has not eaten.
much less slept.

203
00:13:25.096 --> 00:13:26.889
I am more than ready to fly.

204
00:13:26.931 --> 00:13:28.558
[Rhaenyra]
It will not serve us
if your eyes are weary

205
00:13:28.599 --> 00:13:30.435
and your beast fatigued.

206
00:13:30.476 --> 00:13:31.936
I will send Daemon.

207
00:13:33.187 --> 00:13:36.566
I will go once I have dealt
with this business in the city.

208
00:13:36.607 --> 00:13:38.776
Our fallen soldiers.
An accounting must be made.

209
00:13:38.818 --> 00:13:41.237
-Do you not agree?
-I am able. Your Grace.

210
00:13:41.279 --> 00:13:42.947
[Rhaenyra]
The loss to our City Watch

211
00:13:42.989 --> 00:13:45.783
is a crime. to be sure.
but Ser Luthor will investigate.

212
00:13:46.659 --> 00:13:49.245
-It is not a matter
for the crown.
-[Daemon] They are my men.

213
00:13:49.287 --> 00:13:51.998
And we depend
on those men now
to secure your rule.

214
00:13:54.292 --> 00:13:56.544
Especially since their wages
have been withheld.

215
00:14:00.048 --> 00:14:01.549
-Your Grace.
-Not now.

216
00:14:02.967 --> 00:14:04.344
Is it always like this?

217
00:14:05.136 --> 00:14:06.679
Mm.

218
00:14:06.721 --> 00:14:07.972
Daemon.

219
00:14:10.350 --> 00:14:12.477
Have I somehow found myself
back on Dragonstone?

220
00:14:12.518 --> 00:14:14.937
That my voice must again
compete with yours?

221
00:14:14.979 --> 00:14:17.148
On the contrary.
I have pledged to
fulfill your command.

222
00:14:17.190 --> 00:14:18.858
Just... later.

223
00:14:18.900 --> 00:14:21.319
I'm in no mood to jest.
What does it make of me

224
00:14:21.361 --> 00:14:23.654
if you will obey me
only at a time and place
of your own choosing?

225
00:14:23.696 --> 00:14:25.448
You are the queen.

226
00:14:25.490 --> 00:14:27.283
I act in your interest.

227
00:14:27.325 --> 00:14:30.119
Good.
My interest is Vhagar.

228
00:14:30.161 --> 00:14:31.662
Mine too.
But we have time enough.

229
00:14:31.704 --> 00:14:33.331
Aemond is afraid.

230
00:14:33.373 --> 00:14:34.832
He has fled
once already before you.

231
00:14:34.874 --> 00:14:37.794
-We are in no danger.
-There is treachery somewhere.

232
00:14:37.835 --> 00:14:39.462
and I seek to uncover it.

233
00:14:39.504 --> 00:14:41.798
What you seek is revenge.

234
00:14:41.839 --> 00:14:43.674
And gods know
I do not grudge you that.

235
00:14:43.716 --> 00:14:45.301
but revenge may wait.

236
00:14:45.343 --> 00:14:47.553
At this moment. there is
a disturbance in your city.

237
00:14:47.595 --> 00:14:49.847
and you. yourself.
are its likely cause.

238
00:14:52.266 --> 00:14:54.685
I did not ask Ser Luthor
to be brutal.

239
00:14:54.727 --> 00:14:57.397
You need not have
asked him anything at all.

240
00:14:57.438 --> 00:14:59.857
Will you let yourself
be rattled by vapid taunts.

241
00:14:59.899 --> 00:15:01.692
by the painting of stripes
on tavern walls?

242
00:15:01.734 --> 00:15:04.737
They are more than taunts.
They are an insult to my sons.

243
00:15:04.779 --> 00:15:06.739
A challenge
to my very legitimacy.

244
00:15:06.781 --> 00:15:08.658
You are the Queen of Dragons.

245
00:15:08.699 --> 00:15:10.827
Your strength
is your legitimacy.

246
00:15:10.868 --> 00:15:12.453
-[Elinda] Your Grace?
-[groans]

247
00:15:13.371 --> 00:15:15.373
[footsteps receding]

248
00:15:18.709 --> 00:15:20.044
Glad news.

249
00:15:20.711 --> 00:15:23.548
Young Prince Joffrey
has returned this hour
from the Vale.

250
00:15:26.467 --> 00:15:28.719
I'm told he's asked for you.

251
00:15:30.388 --> 00:15:33.182
I will come to him
when I'm able.

252
00:15:33.224 --> 00:15:34.809
I'm sure he's tired.

253
00:15:37.562 --> 00:15:39.564
[footsteps receding]

254
00:15:40.481 --> 00:15:42.191
[Larys] It is long past
the nightingale.

255
00:15:42.233 --> 00:15:44.068
[Aegon] I don't care.

256
00:15:44.110 --> 00:15:45.570
Which way is West?

257
00:15:46.571 --> 00:15:47.655
I have no idea.

258
00:15:52.660 --> 00:15:55.705
-If I may say. Your Grace--
-I'm not going back.

259
00:15:55.705 --> 00:15:58.374
-We have nowhere else to go.
-You heard what I did.

260
00:15:58.415 --> 00:16:00.543
Vhagar has been sighted
at Wendish Town.

261
00:16:00.585 --> 00:16:02.545
Two days ago.
Who knows where
she may be now?

262
00:16:02.587 --> 00:16:05.214
Well. Harrenhal. then.
Someone there
will know something.

263
00:16:05.256 --> 00:16:07.550
Look. Aemond must have left
a-- a message or a sign.

264
00:16:07.592 --> 00:16:09.677
-We can pick up his trail.
-It's 100 leagues

265
00:16:09.719 --> 00:16:11.220
to Harrenhal.
Your Grace. and the fields

266
00:16:11.262 --> 00:16:13.556
and woods are teeming
with Rivermen.

267
00:16:13.598 --> 00:16:16.434
This is more than a folly.
It is dangerous.

268
00:16:16.476 --> 00:16:19.562
Fucking seven fucking hells!

269
00:16:19.604 --> 00:16:21.105
[whimpering]

270
00:16:21.147 --> 00:16:23.733
What would you do
if you found him. hm?

271
00:16:23.774 --> 00:16:26.402
Your brother
is a coiled viper.

272
00:16:26.444 --> 00:16:29.405
and you are--
you are hungry.

273
00:16:29.447 --> 00:16:31.616
and broken. and spent.
and we are alone.

274
00:16:31.657 --> 00:16:33.075
If we were to be discovered--

275
00:16:33.117 --> 00:16:35.286
Stop telling me
what I can't do!

276
00:16:38.623 --> 00:16:39.999
This is his fault.

277
00:16:41.209 --> 00:16:42.210
Everything.

278
00:16:43.294 --> 00:16:45.838
Every one of my miseries
is of his making.

279
00:16:45.880 --> 00:16:48.257
and I swear
before the Warrior himself.

280
00:16:48.299 --> 00:16:51.093
I'm going to find him
and fucking kill him

281
00:16:51.135 --> 00:16:52.720
or die in the attempt.

282
00:16:53.971 --> 00:16:54.972
Hm.

283
00:17:03.648 --> 00:17:04.732
[sighs]

284
00:17:18.496 --> 00:17:19.997
You know me. I think.

285
00:17:22.333 --> 00:17:23.459
By reputation.

286
00:17:23.501 --> 00:17:25.502
It is my privilege now
to listen

287
00:17:25.545 --> 00:17:28.631
to the whispers
of the Red Keep.

288
00:17:28.673 --> 00:17:31.008
-The guests you receive...
-What is it that you want?

289
00:17:31.050 --> 00:17:33.844
...and the gifts they bring.

290
00:17:35.763 --> 00:17:37.223
Show it to me.

291
00:17:40.309 --> 00:17:41.519
[sighs]

292
00:17:53.364 --> 00:17:55.074
My daughter has been unwell.

293
00:17:55.116 --> 00:17:57.493
As you see. she suffers
terrible headaches.

294
00:17:57.535 --> 00:18:01.038
The maester is kind enough
to tend to her.

295
00:18:01.080 --> 00:18:03.416
And yet the flask is full.

296
00:18:05.543 --> 00:18:06.794
[sniffing]

297
00:18:08.629 --> 00:18:10.881
I took a lover after Viserys.

298
00:18:11.882 --> 00:18:13.217
The queen herself
knows the truth of it.

299
00:18:13.259 --> 00:18:15.428
I was careless.
to my shame.

300
00:18:19.390 --> 00:18:21.934
It's a difficult thing.
but I should no longer delay.

301
00:18:26.063 --> 00:18:28.399
[gulping]

302
00:18:28.441 --> 00:18:30.443
[coughing]

303
00:18:33.988 --> 00:18:37.116
Was he a lord or a commoner?

304
00:18:37.158 --> 00:18:39.076
Or perhaps both?

305
00:18:41.912 --> 00:18:44.498
I must appeal to you.
Lady Mysaria.

306
00:18:46.250 --> 00:18:48.419
You of all people
must understand the...

307
00:18:49.587 --> 00:18:52.423
the indignities
we women endure.

308
00:18:54.467 --> 00:18:56.636
There is surely no need for this
to be spoken of again.

309
00:18:56.677 --> 00:18:59.764
You would not. of course.
seek to deceive the queen.

310
00:19:02.266 --> 00:19:04.143
I am her prisoner.

311
00:19:06.270 --> 00:19:08.189
As you were once.
if I'm not mistaken.

312
00:19:14.987 --> 00:19:16.822
As you say.

313
00:19:23.537 --> 00:19:24.955
Have you ever seen
the Hightower

314
00:19:24.997 --> 00:19:26.457
at Oldtown. Ser Criston?

315
00:19:27.458 --> 00:19:28.626
I've heard tell of it.

316
00:19:29.794 --> 00:19:31.796
Ormund and I had a game.

317
00:19:32.630 --> 00:19:34.006
to "run the tower."

318
00:19:35.216 --> 00:19:37.134
You'd start at the base
before dawn

319
00:19:37.176 --> 00:19:39.470
and aim to be the first one
to see the sun rise

320
00:19:39.512 --> 00:19:41.097
from the beacon.

321
00:19:41.138 --> 00:19:42.973
Of course. I let him win.

322
00:19:43.974 --> 00:19:45.810
He was a thin-skinned twat
even then.

323
00:19:46.811 --> 00:19:48.646
Mm.

324
00:19:48.688 --> 00:19:51.649
At that moment.
when the sun rises

325
00:19:51.691 --> 00:19:54.026
over the Seven Kingdoms.

326
00:19:54.068 --> 00:19:55.986
hundreds and hundreds
of miles...

327
00:19:57.697 --> 00:19:59.990
I hope to show it
to you one day.

328
00:20:01.701 --> 00:20:03.953
You could make a home
at Oldtown. Ser Criston.

329
00:20:03.953 --> 00:20:06.747
A knight of your stature
would be most welcome...

330
00:20:08.541 --> 00:20:10.167
to serve our house there.

331
00:20:12.878 --> 00:20:15.172
[horse whinnying]

332
00:20:16.674 --> 00:20:18.592
Halt! Stay back!

333
00:20:19.719 --> 00:20:21.846
[horse whinnying]

334
00:20:23.889 --> 00:20:25.599
Stay clear!

335
00:20:27.935 --> 00:20:29.770
-[whinnying continues]
-[Criston] Hold your ground!

336
00:20:31.188 --> 00:20:32.523
Stand your ground!

337
00:20:35.776 --> 00:20:37.778
[whinnying continues]

338
00:20:42.408 --> 00:20:44.577
-[horse neighing]
-Crow's feet.

339
00:20:45.786 --> 00:20:46.996
Gods.

340
00:20:47.037 --> 00:20:48.831
Are they ahead of us?

341
00:20:48.873 --> 00:20:51.709
[horses neighing. crying]

342
00:20:58.716 --> 00:20:59.884
[sword thuds]

343
00:21:09.477 --> 00:21:10.978
[sighs]

344
00:21:13.606 --> 00:21:16.609
[♪ somber music playing]

345
00:21:40.591 --> 00:21:43.219
[Daemon]
Your hand was heavier
than warranted by the crime.

346
00:21:43.260 --> 00:21:46.388
I was well schooled
in those manners. was I not?

347
00:21:46.430 --> 00:21:48.182
I had the finest of captains.

348
00:21:49.642 --> 00:21:52.436
In any case.
the queen wanted it stopped.

349
00:21:52.478 --> 00:21:55.064
The queen's son is dead.
She must be excused
her impulses.

350
00:21:55.105 --> 00:21:58.234
-Oh. you'd have me refuse her?
-No. rather temper her.

351
00:21:58.275 --> 00:21:59.902
Tend to her humors.
Not every whim

352
00:21:59.944 --> 00:22:01.821
needs to be pursued
with equal vigor.

353
00:22:01.862 --> 00:22:04.657
You know. they cut their bowels
as well as their throat.

354
00:22:04.698 --> 00:22:06.242
Did they tell you that?

355
00:22:06.283 --> 00:22:09.453
Good men dying in agony
in their own shit.

356
00:22:10.454 --> 00:22:11.997
We will pay the villains
back in kind.

357
00:22:12.039 --> 00:22:13.916
What is the mood
among the men?

358
00:22:13.958 --> 00:22:15.918
They complain about their wages.
or lack of them.

359
00:22:15.960 --> 00:22:17.419
-I shall address them.
-[chuckles]

360
00:22:17.461 --> 00:22:19.922
A rousing speech from
the Rogue Prince himself.

361
00:22:19.964 --> 00:22:22.174
I'm not sure
that's gonna make up
for a steady wage anymore.

362
00:22:22.216 --> 00:22:24.093
If I lead them.
they will follow.

363
00:22:24.134 --> 00:22:26.136
It's been a minute

364
00:22:26.178 --> 00:22:28.430
since you were
the Prince of Flea Bottom.

365
00:22:28.472 --> 00:22:31.809
Most of the men were in
swaddling clothes when you--

366
00:22:31.851 --> 00:22:34.061
-[man shouting]
-[people screaming]

367
00:22:36.146 --> 00:22:37.481
[shouting continues]

368
00:22:39.567 --> 00:22:41.569
[bell ringing]

369
00:22:43.863 --> 00:22:45.865
-[people exclaiming]
-[insects buzzing]

370
00:22:56.667 --> 00:22:59.670
[♪ dramatic music playing]

371
00:23:16.353 --> 00:23:18.105
[pigeon cooing]

372
00:23:32.703 --> 00:23:34.079
What is our standing?

373
00:23:34.121 --> 00:23:36.415
Battlements are being raised
with haste. my lord.

374
00:23:36.457 --> 00:23:40.878
But we lack in timber.
and men. and time.

375
00:23:40.920 --> 00:23:43.005
Then levy more conscripts.

376
00:23:43.047 --> 00:23:45.674
and fell every tree
from here to Bitterbridge.

377
00:23:45.716 --> 00:23:47.259
We must secure our walls.

378
00:23:47.301 --> 00:23:48.928
Rhaenyra's host is surely
on the march.

379
00:23:50.304 --> 00:23:53.557
The maester tells me you've been
most assiduous in your lessons.

380
00:23:55.309 --> 00:23:57.519
We are making a study
on my forebears

381
00:23:57.561 --> 00:23:59.271
on the Hightower side.

382
00:23:59.313 --> 00:24:02.858
I mean. their battles.
their enemies.

383
00:24:02.900 --> 00:24:04.902
It has been three days
now spent in the pursuit

384
00:24:04.944 --> 00:24:06.320
of these dry histories.

385
00:24:09.782 --> 00:24:11.325
Dry. did you say?

386
00:24:13.786 --> 00:24:15.579
No. Of course not.

387
00:24:18.415 --> 00:24:21.210
Or rather. they may
seem dry at first glance.

388
00:24:21.251 --> 00:24:22.795
but to learn fr...

389
00:24:24.088 --> 00:24:26.966
To venerate our ancestors.

390
00:24:27.007 --> 00:24:28.801
that is a noble task.

391
00:24:28.842 --> 00:24:30.594
And I'm grateful for it.

392
00:24:31.720 --> 00:24:33.305
Good.

393
00:24:33.347 --> 00:24:35.516
It would please me
to hear you recite.

394
00:24:39.687 --> 00:24:42.147
We have parsed out
the conflicts

395
00:24:42.189 --> 00:24:46.819
between House Greyjoy
and Houses Peake

396
00:24:46.860 --> 00:24:48.904
and Osgrey and Gardener.

397
00:24:48.946 --> 00:24:50.114
House Dayne of Dorne--

398
00:24:50.155 --> 00:24:51.699
And Meria Martell?

399
00:24:53.492 --> 00:24:55.494
The Yellow Toad of Dorne.

400
00:24:58.831 --> 00:25:00.666
I should have a word
with your tutor.

401
00:25:02.292 --> 00:25:04.586
She was the only woman
ever to have been gifted

402
00:25:04.628 --> 00:25:07.006
with a truly military mind.

403
00:25:09.174 --> 00:25:12.302
Though the gods divested her
of beauty in turn.

404
00:25:13.137 --> 00:25:14.638
A blind princess.

405
00:25:14.680 --> 00:25:17.808
Hideous. hairless.
thick of waist.

406
00:25:19.393 --> 00:25:21.729
She does not sound
so formidable.

407
00:25:24.314 --> 00:25:26.316
When Aegon the Conqueror
claimed her lands.

408
00:25:26.358 --> 00:25:27.693
she refused to submit.

409
00:25:29.028 --> 00:25:30.946
She declared him a usurper.

410
00:25:30.988 --> 00:25:32.489
And all those
that marched for him.

411
00:25:32.531 --> 00:25:33.991
traitors to the Seven Kingdoms.

412
00:25:35.367 --> 00:25:38.120
And she swore that Dorne

413
00:25:38.162 --> 00:25:40.372
would ever be unbowed. unbent.

414
00:25:44.752 --> 00:25:45.753
[sighs]

415
00:25:47.046 --> 00:25:50.174
A great host descended
from the Red Mountains.

416
00:25:50.215 --> 00:25:52.551
we Hightowers
regrettably among them.

417
00:25:52.593 --> 00:25:54.470
Meria poisoned her own wells.

418
00:25:54.511 --> 00:25:57.264
hid her soldiers
in the very sand of the desert.

419
00:25:58.390 --> 00:26:00.476
Her castle.
when they found it. was empty.

420
00:26:00.517 --> 00:26:02.978
They thought that
she was vanquished.

421
00:26:03.020 --> 00:26:04.855
But she rose up
out of the darkness

422
00:26:04.897 --> 00:26:07.066
and slaughtered them
in their beds.

423
00:26:09.276 --> 00:26:12.529
Is she a hero. then?
Or a villain?

424
00:26:19.286 --> 00:26:22.831
The Targaryens knew
nothing of our civilization.

425
00:26:22.873 --> 00:26:24.416
the Faith. the Citadel.

426
00:26:24.458 --> 00:26:26.251
What they had.

427
00:26:26.293 --> 00:26:29.755
what they still have.
is strength.

428
00:26:31.090 --> 00:26:33.550
Their armies.
the obscenity of their dragons.

429
00:26:34.259 --> 00:26:36.887
Meria Martell
outwitted her enemy.

430
00:26:37.805 --> 00:26:42.059
A cunning mind can resist
the most savage of beasts.

431
00:26:43.393 --> 00:26:46.939
And Dorne remains
unbroken even today.

432
00:27:04.832 --> 00:27:05.999
I was lucky.

433
00:27:07.334 --> 00:27:09.586
[scoffs] Let us start again.

434
00:27:12.631 --> 00:27:14.633
[pieces clattering]

435
00:27:32.317 --> 00:27:34.778
Never apologize for victory.

436
00:27:43.954 --> 00:27:45.497
I have had these made.

437
00:27:56.133 --> 00:27:57.551
Do you think it
a good likeness?

438
00:28:00.137 --> 00:28:04.016
You are the sign our allies
have been waiting for.

439
00:28:04.057 --> 00:28:07.978
The son of Viserys.
the beacon shining
from the High Tower.

440
00:28:09.313 --> 00:28:11.148
From the lowliest
of the faithful

441
00:28:11.190 --> 00:28:13.066
to Borros Baratheon himself.

442
00:28:17.654 --> 00:28:19.865
[birdsong]

443
00:28:19.907 --> 00:28:22.326
Oh. No. you can't touch that.

444
00:28:23.577 --> 00:28:24.828
Helaena?

445
00:28:27.164 --> 00:28:28.373
Do you know why?

446
00:28:29.333 --> 00:28:31.293
They eat the leaves
of the nightshade.

447
00:28:31.335 --> 00:28:33.170
but that would be death
for you or me.

448
00:28:33.212 --> 00:28:34.463
It's a puzzle.

449
00:28:34.504 --> 00:28:35.923
Jaehaera. come with me.

450
00:28:41.678 --> 00:28:42.930
Come.

451
00:28:47.684 --> 00:28:49.853
Listen now. dearest.
We must leave here.

452
00:28:49.895 --> 00:28:51.355
-[scoffs]
-This very evening.

453
00:28:52.981 --> 00:28:54.733
There seems to be
some trouble in the city.

454
00:28:54.775 --> 00:28:58.153
and some of Rhaenyra's soldiers
must go to help the City Watch.

455
00:28:58.195 --> 00:28:59.947
We will have one guard tonight
instead of two.

456
00:29:03.951 --> 00:29:05.327
Your necklace.

457
00:29:05.369 --> 00:29:08.538
I tendered it to a maid.
She will help us.

458
00:29:08.580 --> 00:29:11.375
There is a hidden door that
leads out in Aemond's chamber.

459
00:29:12.251 --> 00:29:13.877
Below the keep
and beyond its walls.

460
00:29:14.711 --> 00:29:17.047
The one the men used
when they came to kill my boy?

461
00:29:19.216 --> 00:29:20.592
The room is Baela's now.

462
00:29:21.885 --> 00:29:23.595
And she will no doubt
be out hunting.

463
00:29:24.721 --> 00:29:26.848
[sighs]
With luck. we may escape

464
00:29:26.848 --> 00:29:29.101
and-- and melt into the streets
of King's Landing.

465
00:29:29.142 --> 00:29:30.727
And Jaehaera?

466
00:29:32.396 --> 00:29:34.773
Her room is guarded.

467
00:29:34.815 --> 00:29:37.734
If she were to cry out.
even once...

468
00:29:38.944 --> 00:29:40.946
-then that would be the end.
-I will not leave her.

469
00:29:42.656 --> 00:29:45.742
The road ahead
will not be safe for her.

470
00:29:45.784 --> 00:29:47.703
Here. she has nursemaids
to care for her.

471
00:29:47.744 --> 00:29:50.622
and-- and Rhaenyra
will-- will not harm her.

472
00:29:50.664 --> 00:29:52.666
Her rivals would never
raise a girl up to rule. and...

473
00:29:53.959 --> 00:29:55.627
and it-- it might be prudent.

474
00:29:55.669 --> 00:29:58.255
in fact. for the queen
to take the child to ward.

475
00:29:58.297 --> 00:30:01.675
We may even be able to--
to send for her one day.

476
00:30:06.471 --> 00:30:07.764
[sighs]

477
00:30:08.932 --> 00:30:10.642
You look away when you lie.

478
00:30:11.768 --> 00:30:12.853
[Alicent stammering]

479
00:30:15.439 --> 00:30:17.566
[Baela] It has been days
since Vhagar was here.

480
00:30:17.607 --> 00:30:19.276
She feeds. then eludes us.

481
00:30:20.402 --> 00:30:23.447
We have traversed the Trident
50 times in the last fortnight.

482
00:30:24.656 --> 00:30:26.742
For now. we must rest.

483
00:30:26.742 --> 00:30:29.745
Could Aemond be crossing
into the Westerlands to hide?

484
00:30:29.786 --> 00:30:31.580
The Lannisters are allies.

485
00:30:31.621 --> 00:30:33.749
and there are caves and crannies
aplenty in those mountains.

486
00:30:33.790 --> 00:30:35.625
And I'll be pleased
to explore them with you

487
00:30:35.667 --> 00:30:37.753
when you've had a sleep
and a meal.

488
00:30:37.794 --> 00:30:39.296
-He may be moving by night--
-Baela!

489
00:30:40.339 --> 00:30:42.674
[dragon screeching]

490
00:30:42.716 --> 00:30:44.801
-My lady.
-It is well enough for you.

491
00:30:44.843 --> 00:30:46.762
The queen sees you
as her talisman.

492
00:30:46.803 --> 00:30:48.347
a sign from the gods. but I--

493
00:30:48.388 --> 00:30:49.765
It wasn't your fault.

494
00:30:49.806 --> 00:30:51.558
She won't look at me.

495
00:30:53.310 --> 00:30:54.895
And I cannot say I blame her.

496
00:30:57.064 --> 00:30:59.274
The truth is. Addam.
I wanted to go.

497
00:30:59.316 --> 00:31:01.026
I saw myself a hero.

498
00:31:02.402 --> 00:31:04.988
Turning the tide
of a great battle and...

499
00:31:06.323 --> 00:31:07.991
proving my worth
to the realm.

500
00:31:08.033 --> 00:31:10.869
I have the same desire.
as do others.

501
00:31:10.911 --> 00:31:13.288
It is pride.
and I am punished for it.

502
00:31:13.330 --> 00:31:14.998
[dragon bellowing]

503
00:31:15.040 --> 00:31:16.541
My future was ordained.

504
00:31:17.834 --> 00:31:19.252
I was one day to be queen.

505
00:31:20.170 --> 00:31:22.631
My path lay straight before me.
and now--

506
00:31:22.672 --> 00:31:24.341
Your path has vanished.

507
00:31:24.383 --> 00:31:26.176
Though it has been replaced.
perhaps.

508
00:31:27.761 --> 00:31:29.137
By an adventure.

509
00:31:29.179 --> 00:31:31.848
I'll be married off.
likely enough.

510
00:31:31.890 --> 00:31:35.644
to some ancient.
self-regarding lord in Pyke.

511
00:31:35.685 --> 00:31:37.479
with enough hoarded gold
to pay Rhaenyra's debts.

512
00:31:37.521 --> 00:31:39.356
And then.
I'll come and find you.

513
00:31:40.357 --> 00:31:41.733
And we'll fly to exile.

514
00:31:43.860 --> 00:31:45.487
But only if we eat first.

515
00:31:45.529 --> 00:31:46.571
[chuckles softly]

516
00:31:47.697 --> 00:31:49.950
[dragon growling]

517
00:31:52.035 --> 00:31:53.412
Vhagar!

518
00:31:55.205 --> 00:31:56.415
She's gone.

519
00:31:58.458 --> 00:31:59.835
No.

520
00:31:59.876 --> 00:32:02.671
No. no. she will not
abandon me.

521
00:32:02.671 --> 00:32:05.048
I know only that she flew
in the night

522
00:32:05.090 --> 00:32:06.633
and I did not see where.

523
00:32:07.717 --> 00:32:09.302
Maybe she was afraid.

524
00:32:15.392 --> 00:32:16.935
Am I a prisoner?

525
00:32:22.774 --> 00:32:24.776
[groaning softly]

526
00:32:29.906 --> 00:32:31.908
[dragon growling]

527
00:32:37.122 --> 00:32:39.124
[dragon bellowing]

528
00:32:40.750 --> 00:32:42.752
[birds squawking]

529
00:32:49.259 --> 00:32:50.594
No.

530
00:32:51.636 --> 00:32:53.638
[panting]

531
00:32:55.557 --> 00:32:57.476
Without her. I'm nothing.

532
00:32:58.768 --> 00:33:01.354
-You are mistaken.
-I must find her.

533
00:33:02.814 --> 00:33:06.276
And how will you do that
if the dragon has fled?

534
00:33:08.111 --> 00:33:09.821
The queen hunts her as well.

535
00:33:12.949 --> 00:33:14.576
The queen?

536
00:33:14.618 --> 00:33:16.870
I told you.
King's Landing has fallen.

537
00:33:18.371 --> 00:33:20.624
I thought I dreamed it.

538
00:33:25.378 --> 00:33:26.505
Aegon?

539
00:33:27.380 --> 00:33:29.466
The queen says he's dead.

540
00:33:30.467 --> 00:33:31.718
And that you killed him.

541
00:33:36.181 --> 00:33:38.642
Though I do not know
how much of that to believe.

542
00:33:40.894 --> 00:33:44.397
He is dead because
he will not let me be.

543
00:33:49.694 --> 00:33:50.987
He...

544
00:33:51.821 --> 00:33:53.240
he tormented me.

545
00:33:56.409 --> 00:33:57.994
My childhood...

546
00:33:58.828 --> 00:34:00.205
I worshiped him.

547
00:34:09.172 --> 00:34:10.757
And yet our mother...

548
00:34:13.842 --> 00:34:15.178
Sometimes...

549
00:34:16.513 --> 00:34:18.348
the child that grieves her...

550
00:34:19.849 --> 00:34:21.851
is the one a mother loves best.

551
00:34:23.103 --> 00:34:24.103
Hm?

552
00:34:28.024 --> 00:34:29.359
Who are you?

553
00:34:32.027 --> 00:34:33.862
One that has been grieved.

554
00:34:37.701 --> 00:34:39.703
[footsteps approaching]

555
00:34:42.246 --> 00:34:43.373
Go on.

556
00:34:44.291 --> 00:34:45.375
Say it.

557
00:34:48.420 --> 00:34:49.879
My dragon is dead.

558
00:34:50.797 --> 00:34:52.215
I'm a pathetic cripple.

559
00:34:53.216 --> 00:34:56.011
And there is
no possible scenario

560
00:34:56.052 --> 00:34:57.721
in which I make it
to Wendish Town

561
00:34:57.762 --> 00:34:59.723
to kill my stupid
fucking brother.

562
00:34:59.764 --> 00:35:01.224
Now as you should say.
should we--

563
00:35:01.266 --> 00:35:03.226
should we return to the camp.
Your Grace?

564
00:35:04.894 --> 00:35:07.731
I do not care to be
discovered here unguarded.

565
00:35:07.772 --> 00:35:09.190
and less so
when darkness falls.

566
00:35:09.232 --> 00:35:11.526
He was Cole's little pet.
do you remember?

567
00:35:11.568 --> 00:35:13.361
A prodigy with the sword.

568
00:35:14.112 --> 00:35:16.573
Father withdrew me from
the tournaments. of course.

569
00:35:17.240 --> 00:35:20.702
Can't even remember
the pretext anymore.

570
00:35:20.744 --> 00:35:23.371
Probably just afraid
that I'd fall off my horse.

571
00:35:23.413 --> 00:35:26.374
So. I had to sit
and applaud him.

572
00:35:26.416 --> 00:35:28.251
Aemond the champion.

573
00:35:30.253 --> 00:35:32.213
And such a quick student.

574
00:35:32.255 --> 00:35:34.591
Fucking fluent
in High Valyrian.

575
00:35:35.967 --> 00:35:39.429
[speaking High Valyrian]

576
00:35:42.432 --> 00:35:44.559
I'm sure he thought
I was a terrible king.

577
00:35:44.601 --> 00:35:46.394
but what I could have been
if I was...

578
00:35:46.394 --> 00:35:49.564
[banging]
...given his fucking advantages.

579
00:35:49.606 --> 00:35:50.899
And Mother indulged him.

580
00:35:50.940 --> 00:35:52.400
She loved him more.
is the truth of it.

581
00:35:52.442 --> 00:35:55.779
Poor darling Aemond
and his scabby little eye.

582
00:35:55.820 --> 00:35:58.657
And now he's killed me.
and the whole fucking
realm knows it.

583
00:36:05.455 --> 00:36:07.957
-I must say. Your Grace.
-What?

584
00:36:07.999 --> 00:36:10.460
All this time
we've been together...

585
00:36:12.796 --> 00:36:14.923
from the moment
you were injured. in fact.

586
00:36:14.964 --> 00:36:17.801
flying drunk into a battle
to which you were not invited...

587
00:36:18.677 --> 00:36:22.305
you've done nothing
but whinge

588
00:36:23.473 --> 00:36:26.101
and self-flagellate
with a tenacity

589
00:36:26.142 --> 00:36:28.353
I find astonishing.

590
00:36:28.395 --> 00:36:32.107
You. who had
every advantage in life.

591
00:36:32.148 --> 00:36:36.111
You. who had every
chance to shine.

592
00:36:36.152 --> 00:36:39.114
Firstborn son.
prince of the realm.

593
00:36:39.155 --> 00:36:41.616
the finest tutors.
the finest knights

594
00:36:41.658 --> 00:36:43.284
instructing you in the sword.

595
00:36:44.202 --> 00:36:47.205
A dragon so beautiful.
they named him
after the sun itself.

596
00:36:49.916 --> 00:36:52.794
You could have risen
to greatness.

597
00:36:53.670 --> 00:36:58.174
But instead. you trampled
your birthright in the mud.

598
00:37:00.927 --> 00:37:02.220
You lazed...

599
00:37:03.430 --> 00:37:05.765
reveling in mediocrity...

600
00:37:06.933 --> 00:37:09.185
fucking anything in sight
and drinking yourself

601
00:37:09.227 --> 00:37:12.021
into oblivion with
your sycophantic friends.

602
00:37:16.359 --> 00:37:17.861
I will tell you the truth.

603
00:37:19.279 --> 00:37:20.864
You were a terrible king.

604
00:37:22.615 --> 00:37:23.950
But worse than that...

605
00:37:25.034 --> 00:37:28.705
you are a terrible man.

606
00:37:31.416 --> 00:37:34.419
[♪ dramatic music playing]

607
00:37:41.217 --> 00:37:43.219
[Daemon laughing]

608
00:37:44.554 --> 00:37:46.389
-Don't.
-[Daemon sighs]

609
00:37:47.640 --> 00:37:49.225
They said you were here.

610
00:37:49.893 --> 00:37:51.352
I thought there
was some mistake.

611
00:37:51.394 --> 00:37:53.188
They require of me.
perhaps.

612
00:37:53.229 --> 00:37:57.108
just some show
of deference. or regard.

613
00:37:57.150 --> 00:37:59.110
-The people or the Seven?
-Both.

614
00:38:00.487 --> 00:38:02.989
There can be no harm
in it. at the least.
You could try it.

615
00:38:07.285 --> 00:38:08.745
[door opens]

616
00:38:17.420 --> 00:38:19.798
Four of my men lie dead.

617
00:38:19.839 --> 00:38:21.424
Six. if you count the two
from yesterday.

618
00:38:21.466 --> 00:38:23.802
All gold cloaks.
all killed in the same way.

619
00:38:24.677 --> 00:38:25.929
Throats cut.

620
00:38:31.184 --> 00:38:33.812
[speaking High Valyrian]

621
00:39:16.479 --> 00:39:19.065
[septons chanting]

622
00:40:44.776 --> 00:40:46.277
You are tired.

623
00:40:50.073 --> 00:40:51.866
You hear the wind
in these vaulted towers

624
00:40:51.908 --> 00:40:53.993
and imagine their omens
when there are none.

625
00:40:56.829 --> 00:40:58.623
Hm? These are men only.

626
00:40:59.666 --> 00:41:01.751
-Nothing more.
-Then why can't you find them?

627
00:41:30.363 --> 00:41:32.281
You are more than this.

628
00:41:36.619 --> 00:41:38.496
[Gwayne]
This costs us precious time.

629
00:41:38.538 --> 00:41:39.914
[Criston]
That is no doubt their goal.

630
00:41:39.956 --> 00:41:41.124
They knew we would
leave the road

631
00:41:41.165 --> 00:41:43.626
when we abandoned
our mounts.

632
00:41:43.668 --> 00:41:46.796
This land may be theirs.
but even they
could not cause thorns

633
00:41:46.838 --> 00:41:50.425
and brambles to spring
from the earth in our path.

634
00:41:50.466 --> 00:41:51.968
And men are talking
of desertion.

635
00:41:52.010 --> 00:41:54.721
Ser Criston. Friend.

636
00:41:56.472 --> 00:41:59.350
They see no sense
in continuing with this plan
and to speak truth.

637
00:41:59.392 --> 00:42:01.269
nor do I. We grow weak.

638
00:42:01.310 --> 00:42:03.646
-Stoney Sept
still lies far ahead.
-Mm.

639
00:42:09.318 --> 00:42:10.987
If we leave the track here...

640
00:42:11.863 --> 00:42:13.614
cut straight
through the lowlands
toward the crossing.

641
00:42:13.656 --> 00:42:15.533
we may yet still
gain a day or two
over Tully's host.

642
00:42:25.668 --> 00:42:27.670
[people chattering]

643
00:42:52.528 --> 00:42:54.363
Just hire the fucking ship.

644
00:43:02.205 --> 00:43:04.207
[man]
What ship might that be?

645
00:43:05.792 --> 00:43:07.376
Seven hells.

646
00:43:14.425 --> 00:43:16.177
[door opens]

647
00:43:16.219 --> 00:43:17.804
[whispering] He's gone.
My lady. be quick.

648
00:43:30.775 --> 00:43:33.861
You said the nurse
would meet us with Jaehaera.

649
00:43:33.903 --> 00:43:35.196
And so she will.
at the other end.

650
00:43:35.238 --> 00:43:37.073
-Where?
-Come. now. Quickly.

651
00:43:46.916 --> 00:43:49.293
Did you imagine
I wouldn't be watching?

652
00:43:51.212 --> 00:43:52.755
-[sighs]
-So it is she

653
00:43:52.797 --> 00:43:54.882
who is with child.

654
00:43:54.924 --> 00:43:56.717
An inconvenient heir.

655
00:43:56.759 --> 00:43:59.137
There is no need
for Rhaenyra to hear
of what transpired tonight.

656
00:43:59.178 --> 00:44:02.098
I will keep no more secrets
from the queen.

657
00:44:02.140 --> 00:44:04.267
And what will be the result
if you tell her?

658
00:44:05.601 --> 00:44:07.436
We are already at her mercy.

659
00:44:08.563 --> 00:44:10.898
In but a short time.
Helaena's condition
will make itself known.

660
00:44:10.940 --> 00:44:13.067
as these things
cannot help but do.

661
00:44:13.109 --> 00:44:14.819
It is not for me to decide.

662
00:44:17.196 --> 00:44:19.240
-[door opens]
-I heard tell of the White Worm.

663
00:44:19.282 --> 00:44:21.784
-[cat mewing]
-Years ago.

664
00:44:22.785 --> 00:44:24.579
She dealt in secrets
and extortion.

665
00:44:24.620 --> 00:44:26.205
and I knew men
who feared her.

666
00:44:28.291 --> 00:44:29.750
She had the cunning
to play all sides.

667
00:44:29.792 --> 00:44:31.752
not just lapdog to the queen.

668
00:44:31.794 --> 00:44:34.964
These are rich words
in the mouth of a Hightower.

669
00:44:35.006 --> 00:44:38.551
I simply urge you
to think of yourself.

670
00:44:39.886 --> 00:44:42.138
There is good
in Rhaenyra. but...

671
00:44:43.139 --> 00:44:45.016
the crown is a weight
that crushes.

672
00:44:49.854 --> 00:44:51.689
Rhaenyra will do in the end
what she has to do.

673
00:44:51.731 --> 00:44:53.816
and what she has to do
will be dire.

674
00:44:55.443 --> 00:44:57.486
There is only one who can walk
that path with her.

675
00:44:57.528 --> 00:44:58.863
and she chose him long ago.

676
00:44:58.905 --> 00:45:00.615
She knows what Daemon is.

677
00:45:00.615 --> 00:45:03.201
They have ever been
two sides of a coin...

678
00:45:03.242 --> 00:45:04.744
as much as she may deny it.

679
00:45:07.663 --> 00:45:10.458
Her attentions
may be on you now.

680
00:45:10.499 --> 00:45:14.253
that you bathe in the warm light
of her gaze. but...

681
00:45:15.838 --> 00:45:17.381
will you stake so high a wager

682
00:45:17.423 --> 00:45:19.800
on the whims
of a dragonrider?

683
00:45:19.842 --> 00:45:21.552
[Helaena]
I want to go out.

684
00:45:23.679 --> 00:45:25.348
-Not now. dearest.
-Yes.

685
00:45:27.850 --> 00:45:29.352
I need to see the moon.

686
00:45:29.393 --> 00:45:31.187
The window will have to do.

687
00:45:32.605 --> 00:45:34.649
Speak.
and you serve no one.

688
00:45:34.690 --> 00:45:36.150
you gain the queen
no advantage.

689
00:45:36.192 --> 00:45:40.488
But if you say nothing.
no harm is done.

690
00:45:40.529 --> 00:45:42.615
You earn yourself favor
with the Hightowers...

691
00:45:45.618 --> 00:45:47.745
if a time should come
when you have need of it.

692
00:45:58.256 --> 00:45:59.632
[door closes]

693
00:46:00.716 --> 00:46:01.884
[sighs]

694
00:46:15.189 --> 00:46:17.400
He tried to stay awake
for you. Your Grace.

695
00:46:22.446 --> 00:46:25.074
[knight]
Come on. keep moving!

696
00:46:25.116 --> 00:46:27.034
Keep moving now!

697
00:46:27.076 --> 00:46:30.830
[♪ dramatic music playing]

698
00:46:44.844 --> 00:46:46.846
[thunder rumbling]

699
00:46:51.600 --> 00:46:53.269
Forward.

700
00:46:57.857 --> 00:47:00.818
Leave him!
Leave him where he fell.

701
00:47:04.280 --> 00:47:06.657
[thunder continues rumbling]

702
00:47:16.375 --> 00:47:18.377
[grunting]

703
00:47:21.172 --> 00:47:24.175
[♪ dramatic music
continues playing]

704
00:47:44.862 --> 00:47:47.948
♪♪

705
00:47:47.990 --> 00:47:49.992
[wind whooshing]

706
00:47:59.418 --> 00:48:00.836
[grunting]

707
00:48:12.598 --> 00:48:13.974
Where is he?

708
00:48:14.016 --> 00:48:16.018
Aemond One-Eye.
We know he's been here.

709
00:48:16.936 --> 00:48:19.063
Good ser.
this has become tiresome.

710
00:48:20.231 --> 00:48:22.691
I'm of a mind to send a message
to the queen myself.

711
00:48:22.733 --> 00:48:24.235
He's not here.

712
00:48:24.276 --> 00:48:26.487
-He has never been here.
-[sellsword] She's lying.

713
00:48:26.529 --> 00:48:28.739
I've heard about you. witch.

714
00:48:28.781 --> 00:48:31.367
She's no witch.
She's an imbecile.

715
00:48:32.118 --> 00:48:34.912
Cast out and wandering.
Touched in the head.

716
00:48:34.954 --> 00:48:36.664
Though not in the cunny
for too long. I think.

717
00:48:36.705 --> 00:48:38.165
Will you speak to me thus

718
00:48:38.207 --> 00:48:39.875
in the very shadow
of my fortress?

719
00:48:39.917 --> 00:48:41.752
It's been weeks
since I've had a woman.

720
00:48:41.794 --> 00:48:44.338
I'm going to fuck you
and make you my salt wife.

721
00:48:44.380 --> 00:48:46.465
[grunting]

722
00:48:47.550 --> 00:48:48.926
[others chuckle]

723
00:48:48.968 --> 00:48:50.302
[gasps]

724
00:48:55.558 --> 00:48:56.600
[gasps]

725
00:48:58.811 --> 00:49:00.980
Ah! [grunting]

726
00:49:01.981 --> 00:49:03.065
[exclaiming]

727
00:49:03.107 --> 00:49:04.400
-[flesh squelching]
-[groaning]

728
00:49:13.242 --> 00:49:14.743
-[thud]
-[grunting]

729
00:49:14.785 --> 00:49:17.121
-[flesh squelching]
-[gasping]

730
00:49:20.916 --> 00:49:22.918
[panting]

731
00:49:24.753 --> 00:49:26.755
Seems you've taken a turn
for the better.

732
00:49:31.927 --> 00:49:33.929
[crowd clamoring]

733
00:49:36.932 --> 00:49:38.476
[Larys]
In Essos. we can
secrete His Grace

734
00:49:38.517 --> 00:49:40.144
until the time is right
for his return.

735
00:49:40.186 --> 00:49:43.272
But we are watched now.
We can linger here no longer.

736
00:49:43.314 --> 00:49:45.649
-You risk his safety
merely by speaking--
-An ocean passage beset

737
00:49:45.691 --> 00:49:49.069
by pirates. and dragons.
and storms. and then what?

738
00:49:49.111 --> 00:49:51.405
Eating dates and incense
while Westeros

739
00:49:51.447 --> 00:49:53.908
-is reduced to ash?
-His Grace is in
no state to fight.

740
00:49:53.949 --> 00:49:56.744
Neither would he tolerate
the Braavosi heat.

741
00:49:56.785 --> 00:49:59.079
-The monkeys alone--
-You surprise me. Lannister.

742
00:49:59.121 --> 00:50:00.664
Such a distaste
for the foreign.

743
00:50:00.706 --> 00:50:02.208
[Tyland] I have lived
with these people.

744
00:50:02.249 --> 00:50:04.001
Do you forget?
I've eaten with them.

745
00:50:04.043 --> 00:50:06.378
fought with them.
shared everything
with them. even their...

746
00:50:08.130 --> 00:50:09.381
Yes?

747
00:50:10.299 --> 00:50:11.634
I know what they are.

748
00:50:13.511 --> 00:50:15.763
In Braavos. I have prepared
the means for us

749
00:50:15.804 --> 00:50:17.973
to live in a manner
as befits His Grace.

750
00:50:18.015 --> 00:50:19.767
-We can ascertain--
-He is the king. Larys.

751
00:50:19.808 --> 00:50:22.770
Not some chip for you to hold
until such time as benefits you.

752
00:50:22.811 --> 00:50:25.189
-I have men riding with me--
-Sellswords.

753
00:50:25.231 --> 00:50:26.690
Cheaply bought.
by the look of them.

754
00:50:26.732 --> 00:50:28.776
We need only bring him
to Lannisport.

755
00:50:28.817 --> 00:50:30.361
where he will be sheltered.

756
00:50:30.402 --> 00:50:32.530
From there. we may summon
and command what strength

757
00:50:32.571 --> 00:50:34.490
-remains to us.
-Yes. no doubt it would be
the making of the Lannisters

758
00:50:34.532 --> 00:50:36.784
to declare Casterly Rock
the new seat of the king.

759
00:50:36.825 --> 00:50:38.327
Do you think even now
of your own advancement?

760
00:50:38.369 --> 00:50:41.330
Oh. begging your pardon.
most selfless of servants.

761
00:50:41.372 --> 00:50:43.207
I was only risking my life
at sea for our common cause.

762
00:50:43.249 --> 00:50:44.959
Gregor. is it?

763
00:50:45.000 --> 00:50:47.253
It seems I missed
the salient moment when
His Grace made you Hand.

764
00:50:48.337 --> 00:50:49.630
-[blade stabbing]
-[grunting]

765
00:50:49.672 --> 00:50:51.840
[muffled screaming]

766
00:50:53.050 --> 00:50:56.178
You may call me "Your Grace."

767
00:50:56.220 --> 00:50:58.222
-[flesh squelching]
-[groaning]

768
00:51:00.724 --> 00:51:02.101
[metal clanging]

769
00:51:08.649 --> 00:51:12.027
There is an evil spirit afoot.
This is no man. I tell you.

770
00:51:12.069 --> 00:51:14.738
Do not shame yourself. Ned.
We're knights. not infants.

771
00:51:14.780 --> 00:51:17.366
But we will find these cravens

772
00:51:17.408 --> 00:51:18.993
and make a grim example
of them.

773
00:51:19.034 --> 00:51:21.912
We are hunters.
Not prey.

774
00:51:21.954 --> 00:51:24.999
-Hunters get paid.
-It's not safe out there!

775
00:51:25.040 --> 00:51:27.376
[gold cloaks shouting]

776
00:51:27.418 --> 00:51:28.711
[Daemon] Enough.

777
00:51:30.045 --> 00:51:31.755
You and I are the protectors
and keepers

778
00:51:31.797 --> 00:51:34.216
of the greatest Citadel
in all of Westeros.

779
00:51:35.718 --> 00:51:37.636
The governing seat
of a mighty realm.

780
00:51:40.931 --> 00:51:44.101
Without the City Watch.
without us...

781
00:51:46.478 --> 00:51:48.647
these streets would echo
with the cries of insurrection.

782
00:51:51.066 --> 00:51:52.735
The alleys of King's Landing
would boil

783
00:51:52.776 --> 00:51:54.445
with corruption and depravity.

784
00:51:54.486 --> 00:51:57.031
I look to you now
to uphold your vows

785
00:51:57.072 --> 00:51:58.907
to the city and to the throne.

786
00:51:58.949 --> 00:52:01.035
Trust in your queen.
and I pledge you.

787
00:52:01.076 --> 00:52:03.537
you will be repaid twice over

788
00:52:03.579 --> 00:52:05.623
for the sacrifices
you make now.

789
00:52:05.664 --> 00:52:08.250
[all agreeing]

790
00:52:08.292 --> 00:52:09.960
And in the years to come.

791
00:52:10.002 --> 00:52:11.879
as Dorne finally
bends the knee...

792
00:52:11.920 --> 00:52:14.048
[all cheering]

793
00:52:14.089 --> 00:52:15.716
...as Rhaenyra's
great empire grows

794
00:52:15.758 --> 00:52:18.135
and the Seven Kingdoms
become Nine.

795
00:52:18.177 --> 00:52:21.555
become Twelve.
become the new Valyria.

796
00:52:21.555 --> 00:52:24.308
-[all cheering]
-When I return with wagons

797
00:52:24.350 --> 00:52:26.226
spilling over with silks
and silver.

798
00:52:26.268 --> 00:52:29.438
-who will be the first...
-[men shouting]

799
00:52:29.480 --> 00:52:31.940
...to celebrate in the spoils
of conquest?

800
00:52:31.982 --> 00:52:34.318
-[all] We will!
-[shouting continues]

801
00:52:34.360 --> 00:52:35.903
Groups of three and four!

802
00:52:35.944 --> 00:52:38.072
No man walks alone.

803
00:52:38.072 --> 00:52:41.575
Woodgard. Owtram.
you oversee the market square.

804
00:52:41.617 --> 00:52:44.411
[men chattering]

805
00:52:44.453 --> 00:52:45.829
It seems
the Lord of Flea Bottom

806
00:52:45.871 --> 00:52:47.623
has not been
altogether forgotten.

807
00:52:47.665 --> 00:52:49.833
We've apprehended someone.
Your Grace.

808
00:52:49.875 --> 00:52:51.251
At River Row.

809
00:52:51.835 --> 00:52:53.796
Then he will be the first
to be repaid.

810
00:52:56.006 --> 00:52:57.758
Fall in!

811
00:52:57.800 --> 00:52:59.802
Stoney Sept beyond the rise!

812
00:53:04.640 --> 00:53:07.643
[♪ dramatic music playing]

813
00:53:21.865 --> 00:53:23.325
What is it?

814
00:53:26.495 --> 00:53:28.205
The Rivermen have crossed.

815
00:53:29.665 --> 00:53:31.250
And burned the bridge
behind them.

816
00:53:33.168 --> 00:53:35.713
We can no longer delay
their march.

817
00:53:37.840 --> 00:53:39.842
[Panting. sniffling]

818
00:53:40.884 --> 00:53:42.219
So we failed.

819
00:53:59.695 --> 00:54:01.488
-[man screaming]
-[flesh squelching]

820
00:54:01.530 --> 00:54:03.699
[screaming continues]

821
00:54:06.869 --> 00:54:08.871
[man wailing]

822
00:54:11.582 --> 00:54:12.958
[blade scraping]

823
00:54:15.794 --> 00:54:16.795
[gasps]

824
00:54:17.963 --> 00:54:19.339
How many others?

825
00:54:19.381 --> 00:54:21.049
Who was with you?

826
00:54:23.051 --> 00:54:24.762
[panicked breathing]

827
00:54:24.803 --> 00:54:27.139
I was the only one.
I swear it.

828
00:54:28.182 --> 00:54:31.185
-I acted alone.
-Under whose instruction?

829
00:54:31.226 --> 00:54:33.520
I never saw his face.
I told you.

830
00:54:33.562 --> 00:54:35.022
The tongue or the eye?

831
00:54:35.063 --> 00:54:37.065
[panicked breathing continues]

832
00:54:38.942 --> 00:54:41.361
-The eye.
-[yelping]

833
00:54:41.403 --> 00:54:44.239
It was the king. he said!
Please!

834
00:54:46.200 --> 00:54:48.535
He said it was the king's work
I was to be about.

835
00:54:48.577 --> 00:54:49.953
It was Aegon then.

836
00:54:51.914 --> 00:54:53.165
No.

837
00:54:54.833 --> 00:54:56.418
L-Look.

838
00:54:57.252 --> 00:54:58.629
[feet thudding]

839
00:54:58.670 --> 00:55:00.172
In my boot.

840
00:55:05.093 --> 00:55:08.096
Compliments of King
Daeron Targaryen. he said.

841
00:55:09.097 --> 00:55:11.934
For killing traitors
to his throne.

842
00:55:19.691 --> 00:55:21.568
-[sword unsheathing]
-No!

843
00:55:21.610 --> 00:55:23.570
No! No! Please!

844
00:55:23.612 --> 00:55:25.197
[screaming]

845
00:55:28.534 --> 00:55:30.452
[Gwayne] There's none who
may say that you did not give

846
00:55:30.494 --> 00:55:32.162
your best effort.

847
00:55:32.204 --> 00:55:36.124
Perhaps this is the best
we could have hoped for.

848
00:55:37.125 --> 00:55:41.171
We've made our mark
and returned alive...

849
00:55:41.213 --> 00:55:42.923
[sniffling]

850
00:55:42.965 --> 00:55:44.466
...to Tumbleton. perhaps...

851
00:55:45.968 --> 00:55:47.970
to find out what Ormund
has planned.

852
00:55:50.556 --> 00:55:52.724
I thank you for your offer.
Ser Gwayne.

853
00:55:54.977 --> 00:55:56.645
But my path is set before me.

854
00:55:58.647 --> 00:56:01.984
-[clearing throat]
-And what is--
what is that path?

855
00:56:03.569 --> 00:56:05.195
We'll raft the river.

856
00:56:06.196 --> 00:56:08.240
-Or swim it.
-[scoffs]

857
00:56:09.324 --> 00:56:11.660
It was one thing
to obstruct them.
Ser Criston. but...

858
00:56:13.370 --> 00:56:15.664
you must see they've gained
the advantage.

859
00:56:17.249 --> 00:56:18.542
What more can we do?

860
00:56:18.584 --> 00:56:20.252
We will join them...

861
00:56:21.336 --> 00:56:22.880
in battle.

862
00:56:23.755 --> 00:56:25.799
Face them head on.

863
00:56:25.841 --> 00:56:27.926
We have half the men
that we set out with.

864
00:56:29.511 --> 00:56:31.722
There are 200 Rivermen
for every one of us.

865
00:56:32.764 --> 00:56:34.516
That-- you...

866
00:56:35.267 --> 00:56:37.185
It would march us
towards certain death.

867
00:56:39.354 --> 00:56:41.356
-[swords thwacking]
-[foliage rustling]

868
00:56:45.944 --> 00:56:48.030
[birdsong]

869
00:56:52.200 --> 00:56:55.203
This was your goal.
wasn't it?

870
00:56:56.580 --> 00:56:57.789
All along.

871
00:56:58.624 --> 00:57:00.792
Our fate was always assured.
Ser Gwayne.

872
00:57:03.211 --> 00:57:05.088
When we set out.
we were doomed...

873
00:57:06.048 --> 00:57:08.050
to death and defeat.

874
00:57:08.091 --> 00:57:10.719
I have offered you sanctuary.
[sniffling]

875
00:57:11.887 --> 00:57:13.347
Or at least the hope of one.

876
00:57:13.388 --> 00:57:15.390
You have offered me
service to your house.

877
00:57:17.935 --> 00:57:19.561
I am grateful.

878
00:57:22.356 --> 00:57:24.733
But I have-- I have been
a servant all my life.

879
00:57:27.402 --> 00:57:28.987
To green or to black.

880
00:57:31.198 --> 00:57:33.492
I have defined myself
by oaths...

881
00:57:34.910 --> 00:57:36.411
through unyielding devotion.

882
00:57:37.955 --> 00:57:39.414
And the highborn
have made much of me

883
00:57:39.456 --> 00:57:40.999
while it pleased them to do so.

884
00:57:45.253 --> 00:57:47.297
But I will not let them
diminish me now.

885
00:57:50.592 --> 00:57:53.762
I will not return spurned...

886
00:57:55.347 --> 00:57:56.765
rejected.

887
00:57:59.351 --> 00:58:01.436
I am the realm's
greatest warrior.

888
00:58:04.022 --> 00:58:05.691
And I will die as such.

889
00:58:08.026 --> 00:58:09.194
Clear-eyed.

890
00:58:10.612 --> 00:58:11.697
Unbent.

891
00:58:13.490 --> 00:58:14.950
Glorious in battle.

892
00:58:17.160 --> 00:58:20.122
And not in their service.
finally.

893
00:58:22.165 --> 00:58:23.375
But in my own.

894
00:58:28.130 --> 00:58:29.881
And they will sing songs of it.

895
00:58:36.013 --> 00:58:38.056
And Queen Alicent herself
will hear them.

896
00:58:39.516 --> 00:58:42.519
[♪ somber music playing]

897
00:58:46.648 --> 00:58:49.609
The plan is to rebuild
the fleet at Driftmark.

898
00:58:49.651 --> 00:58:51.611
but it will take time.

899
00:58:51.653 --> 00:58:53.488
The Velaryon resources
are diminished.

900
00:58:54.573 --> 00:58:57.159
A condition with which
I am all too familiar.

901
00:58:57.200 --> 00:58:58.869
The king consort. Your Grace.

902
00:58:58.910 --> 00:59:00.454
[footsteps approaching]

903
00:59:00.495 --> 00:59:01.997
My prince.

904
00:59:04.791 --> 00:59:06.752
[Daemon] The price
of our humiliation.

905
00:59:10.005 --> 00:59:12.007
-[Rhaenyra] What is this?
-[Daemon] Who is this.

906
00:59:13.383 --> 00:59:15.635
Young Daeron Targaryen.

907
00:59:15.677 --> 00:59:17.846
Ormund has declared him king.

908
00:59:20.265 --> 00:59:22.184
We should have burned them
when we had the chance.

909
00:59:32.402 --> 00:59:34.488
[Criston]
We have endured much.

910
00:59:34.529 --> 00:59:36.698
Suffered much.

911
00:59:37.616 --> 00:59:39.242
This I know.

912
00:59:41.578 --> 00:59:44.372
And though we languish now...

913
00:59:45.540 --> 00:59:46.750
in the darkness...

914
00:59:48.794 --> 00:59:50.754
we will not lose heart.

915
00:59:50.796 --> 00:59:52.255
[cat mewing]

916
00:59:52.297 --> 00:59:54.007
Come to bed.

917
00:59:54.049 --> 00:59:55.509
[cat mewing]

918
00:59:55.550 --> 00:59:56.927
She hears something.

919
01:00:00.764 --> 01:00:02.849
[mewing continues]

920
01:00:02.891 --> 01:00:05.060
[Criston] The Seven
watch over us even now.

921
01:00:07.479 --> 01:00:09.523
[flame flickering]

922
01:00:09.564 --> 01:00:11.691
[wind whistling]

923
01:00:11.733 --> 01:00:13.151
Look.

924
01:00:19.741 --> 01:00:21.409
[Criston]
Let the Maiden
grant us vision.

925
01:00:22.786 --> 01:00:24.621
For the way ahead
is blessed.

926
01:00:25.747 --> 01:00:28.041
-[grunting]
-[creaking]

927
01:00:28.083 --> 01:00:29.417
[thud]

928
01:00:31.336 --> 01:00:32.629
[gasps lightly]

929
01:00:32.671 --> 01:00:35.132
Let the Warrior
lend us his sword

930
01:00:38.593 --> 01:00:40.595
that we do not falter
in our resolve.

931
01:00:42.305 --> 01:00:43.932
And the Smith...

932
01:00:46.768 --> 01:00:48.145
[softly] Let's go.

933
01:00:49.604 --> 01:00:52.149
Let the Smith bless us
with his strength.

934
01:00:54.818 --> 01:00:56.945
The Crone lights our way.

935
01:00:59.281 --> 01:01:01.825
Ours is the path
of righteousness.

936
01:01:05.871 --> 01:01:07.038
Ser Luthor?

937
01:01:13.128 --> 01:01:14.671
Careful.

938
01:01:14.713 --> 01:01:16.506
[Criston]
The Mother gives her comfort.

939
01:01:17.674 --> 01:01:19.384
The Father. his protection.

940
01:01:20.802 --> 01:01:23.346
No. No. it's blocked.

941
01:01:24.472 --> 01:01:25.640
[whispering]
We have to go back.

942
01:01:25.682 --> 01:01:28.101
There is no way back.
the door is shut!

943
01:01:28.143 --> 01:01:30.145
[rats squeaking]

944
01:01:31.313 --> 01:01:32.355
[cat mewing]

945
01:01:32.397 --> 01:01:33.982
-[hissing]
-[gasps]

946
01:01:35.066 --> 01:01:37.194
No. no. no. no. no! No!

947
01:01:40.155 --> 01:01:41.698
[Criston]
And the Stranger...

948
01:01:45.035 --> 01:01:48.038
[♪ dramatic music playing]

949
01:02:02.219 --> 01:02:04.387
The Stranger offers us rest.

950
01:02:09.226 --> 01:02:12.229
[♪ soft. dramatic music
playing]

950
01:02:13.305 --> 01:03:13.582
-== [ www.OpenSubtitles.org ] ==-
